16/01/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Police arrested two Turkish nationals and an Albanian on Tuesday (January 15th), for suspected involvement in Monday's blast at a steel plant in Elbasan, about 55km south of Tirana. 
The explosion killed one worker and injured six others. 
The three men arrested on Tuesday worked as technicians at the plant and are accused of negligence. 
The blast was caused by a military shell, thrown accidentally into a pile of old iron being prepared for smelting. 
(AP, UPI, B92 - 15/01/08)
